Head of Customer Services - Landside
30 Apr 2014 09:19 PM - UAE
Job Description: Head of Customer Services - LandsideAreas of Responsibility:HalaPax ServicesLost and FoundPurpose of the job:The purpose of this role is to plan, manage and monitor operational performance of all landside areas, ensuring the highest performance standards and safe work environment are met and in line with the Policies and Procedures to deliver consistently our customers’ expectations and achieve or surpass service level agreements with our customer airlines whilst maintaining a stable and positive Industrial Relations climate making us the supplier of choice for our existing and new business.Qualifications & Experience:A bachelor‘s degree / diploma preferably with major course in aviation management, engineering, engineering technology, transportation, business administration or a closely related field.At least 3 years of managerial operations experience monitoring operational activities in an Aviation Industry.Strong ability in developing effective relationships with internal and external stakeholders in order to achieve objectives.A valid UAE Driving license and full maneuvering area driving license will be requiredExcellent knowledge of principles and practices governing the operation of airports as determined by Airport Authority.Familiar with current developments and trends in the field of airport operations, maintenance and management.Proven supervisory methods and techniques in managing airport operations and maintenance staff.SkillsJudgment and Decision Making — Considering the relative costs and benefits of potential actions so as to choose the most appropriate one.Critical Thinking — Using logic and reasoning to identify the strengths and weaknesses of alternative solutions, conclusions or approaches to problemsTo plan, coordinate, monitor, and manage the delivery of the activities and ensure all services are in compliance with company, Customer Airlines and the regulators procedures.To ensure that all company and Airport Authority Policies are adhered to.To install and maintain the necessary procedures so as to ensure that the relevant, Health & Safety and company policy requirements place upon all Landside operations are fully complied with.To consistently provide effective leadership, guidance and support to ensure that all employees are appropriately trained, developed, organized, equipped and motivated to continually deliver achievement of business targets within a stable and positive industrial relations climate.To establish, maintain and develop professional and productive commercial relationships with Airline customers, Airport Authorities and other relevant internal and external bodies.To communicate clearly and concisely with internal departments and customer airlines representatives.To manage within and report upon agreed financial plans and controls to ensure that costs are effectively manage and commercial opportunities are fully exploited to maximize the Landside contribution.To continually monitor, take corrective action where necessary and to communicate standards of operational excellence to ensure that the landside operations functions consistently deliver the quality targets set by our customers and exceed those set by the company.To undertake business projects at the request of the General Manager and to deliver results against objectives, timescales and budgets to contribute to the process of continual business improvement.To ensure direct reports (Hala, Pax Services and Lost & Found) are fully briefed and aware of their roles and responsibilities at all times.To ensure delivery of information to all customers, both internal and external using the communication channels available, ensuring a professional approach at all times.To manage any detailed and complete Incident reports, after full investigation and recommendations for corrective action, as required.To assess the procedures of company continually for possible improvement.To attend Airline customer, airport authority and the regulators’ meetings as required.To manage the highest level of security, safety and service standards are provided by the individual departments and subsequently the company.To provide accurate, comprehensive reporting to General Manager as required.Ensure daily briefings take place, audits are completed and all H&S; rules are being applied in the work place.  Any failures to be immediately addressed with the individuals concerned via management.To effectively manage and support departmental disciplinary matters, ensuring that HR Rules are adhered to and that fully completed records are kept and maintained.To ensure that HR Department and Department Manager are kept fully informed of all disciplinary actions taken within the landside.To ensure written shift report is submitted to General Manager at the end of every shift.To deputise General
